blog.title: me and you
blog.description: lou | 22 | she/her | is this the end of all the endings?

summary:
hey taylor! @taylorswift @taylornation
i’ve been a fan since i found a copy of ‘fearless’ in a music shop at eleven years old- i...
body:
hey taylor! @taylorswift @taylornation

i’ve been a fan since i found a copy of ‘fearless’ in a music shop at eleven years old- i played it in my brother’s ancient CD player and sat cross-legged in wonder at the beautiful voice coming out of the speaker. cue eleven year old me jamming to ‘the way i loved you’ like i’d actually had my heart broken! that same afternoon, i showed it to my sister, and she was enchanted too.

your music saw me through my teenage years- first crushes, heady and naive; the stinging tears brought on my bullies (i remember my mum used to sing ‘mean’ on the way to school to make me feel better); your songs have been the soundtrack to my highest highs and lowest lows. i listen to ‘red’ and i’m driving down country australian highways at dusk, daydreaming. ‘1989’ is melbourne streets, gin and tonic, sugar smiles. and now ‘reputation’, and life on my own, far away from home.

flash forward to now, and i’m about to graduate from uni (i hope to pursue my dream of being a writer!) and my sister is training to be a singer. we spent so many summer evenings absolutely BELTING out ‘the other side of the door’, duetting on guitar. you’ve inspired us with your music, you’ve brought me through some really tough times, but most of all, you’ve made me smile, and you’ve created this beautiful bond between my sister and me.

we were lucky enough to see you at the speak now tour, the red tour, and the 1989 tour, and we’ll be at the reputation show on octiber 26 in melbourne in section L3, row N, seats 67-8. it’s been our life long dream to meet you and thank you for all you’ve done for us xoxo
